];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "How does AI Email work for plasterers?",
    answer: "When a customer or builder emails your business, the AI reads the content, identifies the enquiry, and sends an instant professional acknowledgement. It confirms receipt, captures the key details, and lets the sender know you will follow up. You receive a lead with the full email content and extracted information."
  },
  {
    question: "Does the AI write detailed email replies for me?",
    answer: "No. It sends one professional acknowledgement per email. It does not draft quotes, technical responses, or lengthy replies. The goal is to bridge the gap between their email and your personal follow-up — making sure they know their message was received and you are on it."
  },
  {
    question: "What kind of plastering emails does it handle?",
    answer: "Any inbound enquiry — quote requests from homeowners, specifications from builders, availability checks from landlords, insurance repair briefs from loss adjusters. It does not reply to spam, newsletters, or internal emails."
  },
  {
    question: "Does it work with my existing email address?",
    answer: "Yes. We connect the AI to your existing business email — Gmail, Outlook, or any custom domain address. Setup is handled by our team during onboarding."
  },
  {
    question: "How much does AI Email cost?",
    answer: `AI Email Response is an add-on at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month. Pair it with the Core plan (£${pricing.tiers.core.price}/month).`
  },
  {
    question: "Is email data handled under GDPR?",
    answer: "Yes. All data from email enquiries is managed under UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018. Data is encrypted, stored on UK and EU servers, and shared only with you."
